name: The duties of the president shall be to act as chairman of the Executive Committee
location: and to labor in the general interests of the Conference, as the Executive Committee may advise. Sec. 3. Vice-presidents: The duties of the first vice-president shall be to labor in the European Union Conferences and Missions, as the Executive Committee may advise, and to preside at the councils of the members of the Executive Committee; which may be held in Europe, in -the absence of the president. The duties of the second vice-president shall be to labor in the American Union Conferences and Missions, as the Executive Committee may advise, and, in the absence of the president, to preside at the councils of the members of the Executive Committee which may be held in America. name: The duties of the president shall be to act as chairman of the Executive Committee
location: and to labor in the general interests of the Conference, as the Executive Committee may advise. Sec. 3. Vice-presidents: The duties of the first vice-president shall be to labor in the European Union Conferences and Missions, as the Executive Committee may advise, and to preside at the councils of the members of the Executive Committee, which may be held in Europe, in the absence of the president. The duties of the second vice-president shall be to labor in the American Union Conferences and Missions, as the Executive Committee may advise, and, in the absence of the president, to preside at the councils of the members of .the Executive Committee which may be held in America. name: The duties of the president shall be to act as chairman of the Executive Committee
location: and to labor in the general interests of the Conference, as the Executive Committee may advise. Sec. 3. Vice-presidents: The duties of the first vice-president shall be to labor in the European Union Conferences and Missions, as the Executive Committee may advise, and to preside at the councils of the members of the Executive Committee, which may be held in Europe, in the absence of the president. The duties of the second vice-president shall be to labor in the American Union Conferences and Missions, as the Executive Committee may advise, and, in the absence of the president, to preside at the councils of the members of the Executive Committee which may be held in America.
